n-driven expansion. The disruption time is typically\nof the order of a free-fall timescale, suggesting that the cloud disruption\noccurs rapidly once a sufficiently luminous H II region is formed. We also\ndiscuss limitations of the spherical idealization.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 Jan 2016 20:59:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-23"}
